<paragraph blockId="35.[189,1399,991,1417]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName box="[189,402,991,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchholzi">
<emphasis box="[189,402,991,1018]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Centris buchholzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Herbst" box="[639,808,991,1018]" firstAuthor="Herbst" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="149 - 152" refId="ref20891" refString="Herbst P. 1918. Nuevas avispas antofilas de Chile (Apidae, Hymenoptera). Revista chilena de Historia natural 22: 149 - 152." type="journal article" year="1918">Herbst (1918)</bibRefCitation>
based on male and female specimens collected in Tocopilla, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[458,525,1028,1054]" name="Chile" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Chile</collectingCountry>
. Two males of the type series are housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1065,1132,1028,1054]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="Museum">MCZ</collectionCode>
, one of them with the metasoma missing. The complete male is here designated the 
<typeStatus box="[931,1042,1064,1090]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">lectotype</typeStatus>
, and it has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry box="[263,327,1100,1126]" name="Chile" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Chile</collectingCountry>
<specimenCount box="[336,410,1101,1127]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="generic">190 P.</specimenCount>
Herbst [printed] Nord 
<collectingCountry box="[686,750,1100,1126]" name="Chile" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Chile</collectingCountry>
Tocopilla 
<date box="[878,1001,1100,1126]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1916-10-10">10.X.1916</date>
[handwritten in red ink]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="♂ P. Herbst" authorityName="P. Herbst" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchholzi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Centris buchholzi</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[312,334,1137,1163]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
P. Herbst
</taxonomicName>
in litt. Type [handwritten in red ink]\ P. Herbst Collection [printed]\ [red label] M.C.Z. Type [printed] 23334 [handwritten]\ MCZ-ENT 00023334 [QR code] [printed]. The male 
<typeStatus box="[189,347,1209,1235]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">paralectotype</typeStatus>
has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry box="[717,781,1209,1235]" name="Chile" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Chile</collectingCountry>
<specimenCount box="[792,868,1210,1236]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="generic">190 P.</specimenCount>
Herbst [printed] Nord Tocopilla 
<date box="[1275,1398,1209,1235]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1916-10-10">10.X.1916</date>
[handwritten in red ink]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="♂ P. Herbst" authorityName="P. Herbst" box="[487,840,1246,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buchholzi">
<emphasis box="[487,696,1246,1272]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Centris buchholzi</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[704,726,1246,1272]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
P. Herbst
</taxonomicName>
in litt. Type [handwritten in red ink]\ P. Herbst Collection [printed]\ [red label] M.C.Z. Type [printed] 23334 [handwritten]\ MCZ-ENT 00511493 [QR code] [printed]. The current condition and depository of the female 
<typeStatus box="[1012,1170,1318,1344]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">paralectotype</typeStatus>
are unknown. The fixation of the 
<typeStatus box="[367,475,1355,1381]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">lectotype</typeStatus>
allows confirmation of the synonymy between this species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1926" box="[1246,1399,1355,1381]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilmattae">
<emphasis box="[1246,1399,1355,1381]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">C. wilmattae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zanella" box="[341,518,1391,1417]" firstAuthor="Zanella" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="435 - 488" refId="ref22516" refString="Zanella F. C. V. 2002. Sistematica, filogenia e distribuicao geografica das especies sul-americanas de Centris (Paracentris) Cameron, 1903 e de Centris (Penthemisia) Moure, 1950, incluindo uma analise filogenetica do grupo Centris, sensu Ayala, 1998 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Centridini). Revista brasileira de Entomologia 46 (4): 435 - 488. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262002000400001" type="journal article" year="2002">Zanella (2002)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
